[Category "Competitive Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "competitive_bidding/dont"]
[Student "S"]
{Since partner has entered the bidding in the immediate seat he should have a pretty good hand, with 9+ cards in \Hs and \Ss.

Usually you are happy to settle for partscore after a DONT sequence, but with such an excellent fit for \Hs your hand is worth a raise.

So you bid 3\H and partner says 4\H.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "S"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "S:Q87.AQT8.K2.AJ63 KJ96.K973.AQ65.8 54.J52.JT743.Q42 AT32.64.98.KT975"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "2S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "S"]
1NT pass pass 2C pass 2D pass 2S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "c93034d235d8d91024d3a1fac9cacff945f3b3221824b123ad60a7f124f3e444"]
[Category "Competitive Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "competitive_bidding/dont"]
[Student "S"]
{You have only 7 HCP but expect partner to have a reasonable hand since North could not keep the bidding open. With your black 2-suiter you bid the lowest one, 2\C.

Partner says 2\D.  

Partner's 2\D bid, the next suit up the line, asks you to name your other suit (or pass if your other suit is \Ds).

You bid 2\S and everybody passes.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "5"]
[Dealer "W"]
[Vulnerable "NS"]
[Deal "W:Q94.A42.KJ942.AK AJ73.KQ9.AQ86.63 .T875.73.QJT9542 KT8652.J63.T5.87"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "4S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "W"]
1NT pass pass 2S pass 4S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 5, chOption: S, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 0, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "acdac8596aac3387a0f7630b590d0d9b7e8a80c065c3dd1a0d31c171dd23471d"]
[Category "Competitive Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "competitive_bidding/dont"]
[Student "S"]
{You would have opened 1NT but West beat you to it. You cannot double for penalties when you use DONT, so you pass.

Partner bids 2\S in the balancing seat.  

The 2\S bid shows a weak hand, with more strength partner would have first doubled, then bid 2\S.

Still, you know he has a 6-card suit and you also know that every finesse is going to work. You either bid 3\S or 4\S. Be bold.}

